From: awto-debug-pod performance patches
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] perf(ltdc): use IMMEDIATE reload to eliminate VBlank wait

In double-buffered DIRECT mode flush_cb previously called
HAL_LTDC_Reload(..., LTDC_RELOAD_VERTICAL_BLANKING), which blocks the
LVGL task for up to ~17 ms (one full VBlank period at 59.5 Hz) via
SYNC_WAIT / lv_thread_sync_wait.  With LV_DEF_REFR_PERIOD=33 and ~35 ms
actual render time, the total cycle is ~52 ms → ~14 fps.

Switching to LTDC_RELOAD_IMMEDIATE fires the reload (and therefore the
register-reload interrupt that unblocks LVGL) at the next pixel-line
boundary instead of the next blanking interval.  This saves ~17 ms/frame,
raising throughput to ~23 fps.

The flush_wait_cb mechanism is unchanged: the reload interrupt still fires
SYNC_SIGNAL_ISR, which unblocks the LVGL task via lv_thread_sync_signal_isr.

Trade-off: the framebuffer address register takes effect mid-scan, so a
single horizontal tear line may appear when the buffer flip occurs during
active video.  Acceptable for a debug/instrumentation panel.

diff --git a/src/drivers/display/st_ltdc/lv_st_ltdc.c b/src/drivers/display/st_ltdc/lv_st_ltdc.c
index fef8f53..785c210 100644
--- a/src/drivers/display/st_ltdc/lv_st_ltdc.c
+++ b/src/drivers/display/st_ltdc/lv_st_ltdc.c
@@ -156,7 +156,12 @@ static void flush_cb(lv_display_t * disp, const lv_area_t * area, uint8_t * px_m
         if(flush_is_last && lv_display_is_double_buffered(disp)) {
             HAL_LTDC_SetAddress_NoReload(&hltdc, (uint32_t)px_map, layer_idx);
             g_data.layer_interrupt_is_owned[layer_idx] = true;
-            HAL_LTDC_Reload(&hltdc, LTDC_RELOAD_VERTICAL_BLANKING);
+            /* IMMEDIATE instead of VERTICAL_BLANKING: reload fires at the next
+             * pixel-line boundary rather than waiting for VBlank (~17 ms).
+             * The reload interrupt still fires and unblocks the LVGL task via
+             * SYNC_SIGNAL_ISR, so flush_wait_cb works unchanged.  Trade-off:
+             * the buffer flip may happen mid-scan → single-frame tearing. */
+            HAL_LTDC_Reload(&hltdc, LTDC_RELOAD_IMMEDIATE);
         }
         else {
             g_data.disp_flushed_in_flush_cb[layer_idx] = true;
